4
00:00:55,306 --> 00:00:57,934
Pull it slowly. Then toss it.

5
00:00:58,017 --> 00:01:00,394
Oh, I will move slow.

6
00:01:00,478 --> 00:01:03,606
I ain't tossing nothing, bow tie.

7
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:07,735
So whatever you gonna do, you might
as well go ahead and make it quick.

8
00:01:08,819 --> 00:01:11,864
- I knew you'd come back.
- I trust you didn't lose sleep over it.

9
00:01:12,031 --> 00:01:16,327
Worrying about you would be like
wondering if the sun gonna come up.

10
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:18,412
I ain't about to wild out over it.

11
00:01:19,247 --> 00:01:21,207
What I want to know
is how you find me.

12
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:23,751
Your boy, he didn't give you up easy.

13
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:26,879
Ain't no sugar-water
run through them veins.

14
00:01:26,963 --> 00:01:30,049
- You kill him?
- He's resting.

15
00:01:30,132 --> 00:01:33,511
- I see you favor a .45.
- Tonight I do.

16
00:01:34,512 --> 00:01:37,974
And I keeps one in the chamber,
in case you pondering.

17
00:01:40,059 --> 00:01:41,852
Nice showpiece you got there.

18
00:01:41,936 --> 00:01:45,356
Walther ppk .380, double action.

19
00:01:46,190 --> 00:01:50,444
- Hear them walthers like to jump some.
- As will you, with one in your elbow.

20
00:01:50,528 --> 00:01:53,447
That gun ain't got enough firepower
to make myjoint useless.

21
00:01:53,531 --> 00:01:56,075
It definitely won't stop me
from emptying out half my mag.

22
00:01:56,158 --> 00:02:00,246
- You might not hit me.
- This range? And this caliber?

23
00:02:01,664 --> 00:02:05,084
- Even if I miss, I can't miss.
- I admire a man with confidence.

24
00:02:05,376 --> 00:02:08,629
I don't see no sweat
on your brow neither, bro.

25
00:02:14,093 --> 00:02:16,053
I suppose we could stand here all night.

26
00:02:16,262 --> 00:02:18,931
Suppose we could.

27
00:02:19,015 --> 00:02:20,975
Or settle this once and forever.

28
00:02:26,856 --> 00:02:29,900
I want to ask you something, brother.

29
00:02:35,406 --> 00:02:37,408
Omar listening.

30
00:02:47,043 --> 00:02:49,337
When you walk through the garden

31
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:53,257
you gotta watch your back

32
00:02:54,675 --> 00:02:57,303
well, I beg your pardon

33
00:02:58,304 --> 00:03:00,514
walk the straight and narrow track

34
00:03:00,598 --> 00:03:01,974
walk the straight
and narrow track

35
00:03:02,058 --> 00:03:06,020
if you walk with Jesus

36
00:03:06,103 --> 00:03:08,314
he's gonna save your soul

37
00:03:09,732 --> 00:03:12,109
you gotta keep the devil

38
00:03:13,652 --> 00:03:16,280
way down in the hole

39
00:03:17,573 --> 00:03:20,034
he got fire and the fury

40
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:21,744
fire and fury

41
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,455
at his command

42
00:03:25,456 --> 00:03:28,542
well, you don't have to worry

43
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:32,338
hold on to Jesus' hands

44
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:35,424
oh, we'll be safe from Satan

45
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,969
when the thunder rolls

46
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:43,516
you gotta keep the devil

47
00:03:44,183 --> 00:03:47,144
way down in the hole

48
00:03:55,403 --> 00:03:58,572
You gotta keep the devil

49
00:03:59,323 --> 00:04:01,575
way down in the hole

50
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:06,580
way down

51
00:04:06,664 --> 00:04:09,333
way down in the hole

52
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:33,917
- I'm going to the west.
- All right.

53
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:35,609
- Peace out.
- All right.

54
00:04:37,069 --> 00:04:38,612
Here we go.

55
00:04:44,952 --> 00:04:49,123
- Yo, I need some face time with the man.
- Hold on, I'll holler back at you, man.

56
00:04:49,206 --> 00:04:50,499
That'd be shamrock.

57
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:54,295
Assuming stringer bell is the man,
now we wait for the return call.

58
00:04:55,713 --> 00:04:56,839
This is beautiful.

59
00:04:57,089 --> 00:05:02,178
Lester, can you actually believe we
fucking sold the wiretaps to the targets?

60
00:05:02,261 --> 00:05:04,513
For a week at least.

61
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:10,019
Maybe we ducked a bullet.
Maybe we clean this mess quietly,

62
00:05:10,102 --> 00:05:13,189
throw some horseshit
at whatever reporter shows up

63
00:05:13,272 --> 00:05:15,608
and the mayor forgives and forgets.

64
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:17,359
We're ready to move on this, right?

65
00:05:17,443 --> 00:05:21,530
As soon as we get the word,
we shut down all three zones.

66
00:05:21,614 --> 00:05:24,116
There'll be nothing left
before midnight shift.

67
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,911
So what the fuck are we waiting on
for a day and half?

68
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:29,246
Why isn't the hall calling us?

69
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:40,049
- Mayor's office.
- Commissioner burrell for mayor Royce.

70
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:42,843
- I've heard enough.
- Hold on, Coleman.

71
00:05:42,927 --> 00:05:44,970
- Let the man talk.
- Excuse me, mayor.

72
00:05:45,054 --> 00:05:46,764
I have commissioner burrell on the line.

73
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:49,016
- He says it's urgent.
- I'll bet it is.

74
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,976
He wants to move, Clarence.

75
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,896
He wants to clean this shit up yesterday,
and so do we.

76
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:56,357
Tell him to hold. Go ahead, gene.

77
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:59,443
Look, I'm not a politician,
I'm an academic.

78
00:06:00,152 --> 00:06:02,530
From a public health perspective

79
00:06:02,613 --> 00:06:04,949
there are remarkable things
happening in the free zones.

80
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:09,245
Needle exchanges, on-site blood testing,
condom distribution.

81
00:06:09,328 --> 00:06:13,207
We're interacting with an at-risk community
that is largely elusive.

82
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:15,793
We're even talking some of them
into drug treatment.

83
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:19,046
That's just what um and bon secours
have brought to the table.

84
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:23,425
If this were sanctioned, my department
could put public resources into play.

85
00:06:23,509 --> 00:06:27,304
- You people can't see the forest here.
- Odell?

86
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:32,184
When the story breaks,
the ministers will surely be against you.

87
00:06:32,268 --> 00:06:35,145
And most of the city council
will be walking sideways

88
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:37,147
away from your administration.

89
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:39,775
And my guess is
the governor and the legislature

90
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:43,779
will use this opportunity
to piss on the city from a great height.

91
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:46,073
And Washington? Oooh.

92
00:06:46,156 --> 00:06:49,910
Can you imagine how far
the United States department of justice

93
00:06:49,994 --> 00:06:52,121
is gonna crawl up your ass behind this?

94
00:06:52,204 --> 00:06:54,582
Crime is down, odell.

95
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:58,669
Medical people
are telling me this could work.

96
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:02,423
I mean, a 14% decline in felonies citywide,

97
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:05,843
I might be untouchable on this.
Look, we need to think.

98
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:09,054
See if we can keep this going
without calling it what it really is.

99
00:07:09,138 --> 00:07:11,432
- Jesus.
- Now, there's got to be a way.

100
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:14,685
I want you to talk this thing out.
Erv, thanks for holding.

101
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:16,270
Yes, but...

102
00:07:19,982 --> 00:07:21,525
Yes, I understand.

103
00:07:23,152 --> 00:07:25,279
Then I'll wait to hear from you.

104
00:07:26,614 --> 00:07:29,575
We're to hold off
on any action in hamsterdam.

105
00:07:29,658 --> 00:07:33,537
No arrests,
no movement until further notice.

106
00:07:33,621 --> 00:07:35,623
He says he wants to regroup,

107
00:07:36,498 --> 00:07:39,543
determine the most effective
course of action.

108
00:07:39,627 --> 00:07:43,547
Translate that for me, will you, erv?
I don't speak his fucked-up lingo.

109
00:07:43,631 --> 00:07:47,468
Royce is figuring a way to put
all of us in the guillotine

110
00:07:47,551 --> 00:07:50,888
and keep the blood from
spraying anywhere near the hall.

111
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:53,974
Shit, I'll be goddamned
if I'm gonna go out like that.

112
00:07:54,058 --> 00:07:56,018
Bent over in public.

113
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:58,937
I can spin the story
just as well as that motherfucker.

114
00:07:59,021 --> 00:08:01,732
- You're gonna go to the press?
- Not me.

115
00:08:01,899 --> 00:08:03,233
But I know a slick little bastard

116
00:08:03,317 --> 00:08:06,403
who will happily
put his honor's shit in the street.

117
00:08:09,573 --> 00:08:11,492
Something funny about that?

118
00:08:11,575 --> 00:08:15,996
I look in the paper, and I see all these
federal grants, but nothing for b&b.

119
00:08:17,289 --> 00:08:20,209
- You're expecting what?
- Payout.

120
00:08:20,376 --> 00:08:22,378
A big payout for what we put in, man.

121
00:08:22,461 --> 00:08:24,838
Federal dollars
on them Howard street rehabs.

122
00:08:24,922 --> 00:08:27,174
- You gave money up front?
- $250,000, yeah.

123
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,510
To Clay Davis.

124
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:32,513
How you know?

125
00:08:32,596 --> 00:08:34,890
What you saying? He's running game?

126
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:38,936
- No, hell, no, he ain't that brazen.
- Mm-mm. Let me guess.

127
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:41,230
He's told you about the faucet.

128
00:08:41,313 --> 00:08:44,066
Or was it the goose
that laid the golden egg?

129
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,859
You ever actually meet the man?

130
00:08:45,943 --> 00:08:48,487
Did you see any of your cash
reach anyone in authority?

131
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:50,572
I met the guy at the federal building.

132
00:08:50,656 --> 00:08:52,658
Yeah? What office?

133
00:08:54,326 --> 00:08:56,495
He came down to the lobby.

134
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:05,462
He rainmade you. A guy says if you pay him,
he can make it rain.

135
00:09:05,921 --> 00:09:08,924
You pay him.
If and when it rains, he takes the credit.

136
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:12,261
If and when it doesn't,
he finds reasons for you to pay him more.

137
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:14,054
- Clay Davis rainmade you.
- No, man.

138
00:09:14,138 --> 00:09:16,932
He got them building permits
in no time at all, man.

139
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:20,728
We bribing these motherfuckers.
He got the city contractor's money back.

140
00:09:20,936 --> 00:09:23,021
- How much?
- $35,000 so far.

141
00:09:23,105 --> 00:09:25,691
- On the quarter-million?
- It's for bribing the motherfuckers.

142
00:09:25,774 --> 00:09:27,901
There are no bribes!

143
00:09:28,485 --> 00:09:33,031
You really think a state senator is
going to risk his salary and his position

144
00:09:33,115 --> 00:09:36,368
by walking into a federal office
with a briefcase full of drug money?

145
00:09:36,535 --> 00:09:38,495
I seen chunky, chunky coates.

146
00:09:38,579 --> 00:09:40,664
He gets his money same way everyone does.

147
00:09:40,748 --> 00:09:44,418
He fills out applications, checks
the plans, then prays like hell.

148
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:49,131
This is an old game in this town.
And Clay Davis?

149
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,926
That ganef was born
with his hand in someone's pocket.

150
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:55,179
I just wish you'd run it by me sooner.

151
00:10:08,609 --> 00:10:11,236
Now here's shamrock
returning bodie's call.

152
00:10:12,404 --> 00:10:13,447
Talk about it.

153
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:16,658
The man said he'd see you
same time as always.

154
00:10:16,742 --> 00:10:20,162
During the first call, sydnor had eyes
on shamrock over in west Baltimore.

155
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:22,247
All right? Now look at this.

156
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:26,084
At the time, stringer bell
was at the print shop.

157
00:10:26,168 --> 00:10:28,128
So it couldn't be a face-to-face meet.

158
00:10:28,212 --> 00:10:32,299
We didn't catch a call between stringer
and shamrock. How can that be?

159
00:10:32,382 --> 00:10:35,677
Stringer's phone isn't on the same network
as everyone below him.

160
00:10:35,761 --> 00:10:39,056
- Right you are, ma'am.
- Bell's not using Bernard's burners.

161
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:42,810
And shamrock has a separate phone
for calling bell.

162
00:10:42,893 --> 00:10:46,522
We can't hear those calls
because the system's compartmentalised.

163
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:48,524
Some tricky motherfuckers.

164
00:10:48,607 --> 00:10:51,318
A week or so up on Bernard's phones
and we'll have everybody,

165
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:54,738
up to and including shamrock,
tangled up in conspiracy counts.

166
00:10:54,822 --> 00:10:56,240
But bell or barksdale?

167
00:10:56,406 --> 00:10:59,535
Not unless we can
pluck their cell numbers out of the air.

168
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:04,706
- Where you headed?
- Toy store.

169
00:11:08,252 --> 00:11:13,131
- He iegalised drugs in special zones?
- It's more than that.

170
00:11:13,215 --> 00:11:16,844
Major Colvin lost the necessary perspective

171
00:11:16,927 --> 00:11:18,929
that is required for command.

172
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:22,766
Now, we were all under pressure
to reduce crime before year-end,

173
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:25,644
and he responded poorly to that pressure.

174
00:11:25,936 --> 00:11:28,063
Pressure by who? Mayor?

175
00:11:28,939 --> 00:11:31,441
I'm just explaining to you

176
00:11:31,525 --> 00:11:34,820
that the pressure
was applied all down the line,

177
00:11:34,903 --> 00:11:37,406
from headquarters
to the district commanders,

178
00:11:37,489 --> 00:11:39,867
to the shift and sector supervisors.

179
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:43,453
So Colvin's 14% decline was bullshit.

180
00:11:44,955 --> 00:11:48,208
And they're selling drugs
with police permission in western?

181
00:11:48,292 --> 00:11:53,005
The department is ready
to shut that mess down with mass arrests.

182
00:11:53,088 --> 00:11:55,966
- I'm on top of it.
- Why don't you move?

183
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,510
The mayor says wait.

184
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:04,182
I think he's gonna make some kind of show,

185
00:12:04,266 --> 00:12:07,895
spin it so that I take the weight for
something that has nothing to do with me,

186
00:12:07,978 --> 00:12:12,316
and everything to do with the pressure that
my commanders were getting from city hall.

187
00:12:17,863 --> 00:12:22,367
Going public and putting the responsibility
for this back at city hall

188
00:12:22,451 --> 00:12:24,828
is the only move I have left, right?

189
00:12:25,871 --> 00:12:28,498
I mean, I spin Royce before he spins me.

190
00:12:28,999 --> 00:12:31,168
- And you want me to...
- No, not you.

191
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,170
Your pal, Tony gray.

192
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:37,132
If he's gonna take a run at Royce,
he's gonna need ammunition, right?

193
00:12:41,011 --> 00:12:44,932
I don't have a relationship with gray.
I do have one with you.

194
00:12:45,015 --> 00:12:48,310
And, councilman, you owe me.

195
00:12:54,024 --> 00:12:56,818
- What's up, hotshot?
- I got a technical question.

196
00:12:56,902 --> 00:13:00,113
Remember those units we used to use
to get cell numbers?

197
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:01,949
Cf-something-something.

198
00:13:02,032 --> 00:13:04,159
Cell frequency identification device.

199
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:07,120
- The triggerfish.
- That one. It could flag a number.

200
00:13:07,204 --> 00:13:08,789
Right. With the old machines,

201
00:13:08,872 --> 00:13:11,792
we had to follow the guy
while he used the phone.

202
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:15,671
New digitals? Bing. You just pull
the number right off the cell tower.

203
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:17,547
You got any that daddy can borrow?

204
00:13:17,631 --> 00:13:20,092
- What about yours?
- What?

205
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:22,135
City has three of them, I remember right.

206
00:13:22,219 --> 00:13:25,764
Homeland security sent them to you,
every big county department.

207
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:27,724
No fucking way.

208
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:31,395
Thanks.

209
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:38,235
- I doubted you.
- I told you it was big.

210
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,403
If we play it right.

211
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:42,322
He wants me to turn the information
over to Tony gray.

212
00:13:42,406 --> 00:13:44,908
He figures if Tony's
running against the mayor,

213
00:13:44,992 --> 00:13:46,994
he'll aim at Royce, not the department.

214
00:13:47,077 --> 00:13:50,372
You may want to bring Tony in on it,
keep him viable against the mayor.

215
00:13:50,664 --> 00:13:53,875
But you need to find out
what this is all about. First-hand.

216
00:13:53,959 --> 00:13:57,587
- Do you know this major Colvin?
- To shake hands, maybe.

217
00:13:58,296 --> 00:14:00,424
If burrell's painting him the villain,

218
00:14:00,507 --> 00:14:03,427
Colvin might be anxious
to tell his side of the story.

219
00:14:13,145 --> 00:14:15,063
Mcnulty, major crimes.

220
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:17,441
Sullivan, minor irritations.

221
00:14:19,443 --> 00:14:23,613
You got anything that's like a cfid,
but digital? For catching cell numbers.

222
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:26,533
- Catching who?
- A triggerfish machine.

223
00:14:28,285 --> 00:14:30,954
Triggerfish. For cell numbers.

224
00:14:34,332 --> 00:14:36,960
How about I look around there on my own?

225
00:14:50,891 --> 00:14:52,809
This is councilman carcetti at the hall.

226
00:14:52,976 --> 00:14:55,896
- I'm trying to reach major Colvin.
- He's on vacation.

227
00:14:55,979 --> 00:14:58,565
I'm trying to reach him
on municipal business.

228
00:14:58,648 --> 00:15:00,567
I can put you through to his voicemail.

229
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:03,111
No, I said I have to reach him immediately.

230
00:15:03,195 --> 00:15:05,030
- Immediately?
- Right.

231
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:08,617
- How about his cell phone?
- His cell? Yeah, that would be fine.

232
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:18,376
All right, that's enough.

233
00:15:20,504 --> 00:15:22,297
Yeah, I know, it hurts.

234
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:25,258
But your fists
gonna be like rocks after a while.

235
00:15:29,346 --> 00:15:31,348
Justin, come here.

236
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:37,521
All right, I want you to push me in
my chest. You ain't got to do it hard.

237
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:44,236
- That's how you were standing.
- No weight on your back foot.

238
00:15:44,319 --> 00:15:46,613
That's right. No center of gravity.

239
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,116
