00:34:20,059 --> 00:34:24,230
What did you do, major?
And why the fuck haven't they shut it down?

477
00:34:24,313 --> 00:34:27,233
We've seen that law enforcement's
steamroller approach

478
00:34:27,316 --> 00:34:29,109
is just spitting in the wind!

479
00:34:29,193 --> 00:34:31,487
I really think that you're
onto something here,

480
00:34:31,570 --> 00:34:35,866
but if you keep it up, they'll be calling
you the most dangerous man in america.

481
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:38,953
I know it may appear
that we're vulnerable here, huh?

482
00:34:39,036 --> 00:34:44,083
But if we enforce the drug laws
everywhere else in the city aggressively,

483
00:34:44,166 --> 00:34:47,002
how can they say
we're not a law and order administration?

484
00:34:47,086 --> 00:34:50,339
Now there's got to be a middle ground here
that we have yet to find.

485
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:52,633
There's got to be some way
to accomplish this

486
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:54,551
without turning everything upside down.

487
00:34:55,844 --> 00:34:58,097
This used to be one of my worst corners.

488
00:34:59,431 --> 00:35:01,934
This is where a cop got shot
last summer, right?

489
00:35:02,059 --> 00:35:04,687
- Dozerman.
- Looks quiet now.

490
00:35:07,231 --> 00:35:09,233
So do most all my corners.

491
00:35:14,154 --> 00:35:15,948
G-man.

492
00:35:22,454 --> 00:35:25,541
- So, what's up?
- Shut the door.

493
00:35:31,046 --> 00:35:35,217
In ten minutes we're gonna have
an affidavit for a cityjudge to sign.

494
00:35:35,301 --> 00:35:38,178
- It's for Russell bell's dirty cell.
- It's a good pull.

495
00:35:38,262 --> 00:35:41,890
It is if bay wireless
doesn't take five days to process it.

496
00:35:42,099 --> 00:35:43,976
You owe me, Fitz.

497
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:48,063
That whole port case came down early
behind some ugly shit in your house.

498
00:35:49,898 --> 00:35:54,903
Now, I don't care how you do it,
but I need my wire today.

499
00:35:58,657 --> 00:36:03,996
These guys were in radio cars two months
ago, chasing calls, clearing corners.

500
00:36:04,079 --> 00:36:05,998
I pulled them to do felony follow-up.

501
00:36:06,081 --> 00:36:10,002
More police work, less bullshit,
and that's why my crime is down.

502
00:36:10,961 --> 00:36:12,463
The numbers are true.

503
00:36:14,423 --> 00:36:17,634
- What did he do?
- Church burglaries, 14 of them.

504
00:36:20,346 --> 00:36:22,306
Let's go.

505
00:36:25,267 --> 00:36:26,935
Mademoiselle.

506
00:36:28,145 --> 00:36:31,023
Is it "aff-e-ant" or affiant?

507
00:36:31,106 --> 00:36:33,901
I've never been clear on that.

508
00:36:36,945 --> 00:36:40,532
You been hunting this guy bell
for a long time, haven't you, Jimmy?

509
00:36:40,616 --> 00:36:43,035
A while, yeah.

510
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:44,953
Name's familiar to me.

511
00:36:45,579 --> 00:36:48,332
That thing that we did
a few years back, was he the...

512
00:36:48,415 --> 00:36:50,417
Yeah.

513
00:36:52,211 --> 00:36:54,213
What's done is done, Jimmy.

514
00:36:55,506 --> 00:36:58,008
Now, for your own fucking sake,
just let it go.

515
00:37:00,594 --> 00:37:02,221
Come on.

516
00:37:04,306 --> 00:37:07,309
As the affiant, do you solemnly swear

517
00:37:07,393 --> 00:37:09,937
that the information
contained in this document...

518
00:37:10,729 --> 00:37:14,983
That's the most significant drop in
crime in this district in recent history.

519
00:37:17,820 --> 00:37:20,322
We still got
hard-looking boys out on them streets.

520
00:37:20,489 --> 00:37:23,575
And, sergeant,
you know them little mini-motorcycles?

521
00:37:23,659 --> 00:37:26,912
- They keeping me up at night.
- We're working on that.

522
00:37:26,995 --> 00:37:30,040
I have been living
in this part of the city my whole life.

523
00:37:30,124 --> 00:37:33,252
I can tell you something.
We weren't any angels when we were kids.

524
00:37:33,335 --> 00:37:35,337
And those hard boys you talking about,

525
00:37:35,421 --> 00:37:38,090
half of them, they's just playing gangster.

526
00:37:38,173 --> 00:37:40,551
They ain't no different from what we were.

527
00:37:40,634 --> 00:37:43,137
Shirts and drawers a little longer, is all.

528
00:37:44,638 --> 00:37:47,683
The one thing
I do miss about my neighborhood,

529
00:37:48,016 --> 00:37:49,935
the neighborhood I came up in...

530
00:37:50,018 --> 00:37:52,396
See, we knew the police. See?

531
00:37:52,479 --> 00:37:57,151
We had a white police officer. Our
house was on his beat, on his foot beat.

532
00:37:57,234 --> 00:38:00,571
He would be sitting out talking
to my mother damn near every night,

533
00:38:00,654 --> 00:38:03,031
just sitting out on
her stoop, just talking.

534
00:38:03,115 --> 00:38:06,618
And I'm telling you, this man,
his name was Frazier O'Leary.

535
00:38:06,702 --> 00:38:09,413
- He even knew my grandmother by name.
- Yes, ma'am.

536
00:38:09,496 --> 00:38:11,707
Let's move on
to the tip-line information...

537
00:38:11,874 --> 00:38:14,460
I'm so sorry, baby, but I was not finished.

538
00:38:14,543 --> 00:38:16,628
You see, let me tell you something.

539
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:21,884
I have not seen that face-to-face
policing in a long while.

540
00:38:21,967 --> 00:38:25,053
In a very long while. Until last week.

541
00:38:25,137 --> 00:38:29,892
A young officer, black officer,
came by my stoop, gave me his card.

542
00:38:29,975 --> 00:38:33,437
His name is Reggie Ballard,
is his name, right?

543
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:36,273
And he sat, and he talked to me.
We just talked.

544
00:38:36,356 --> 00:38:40,444
And, see, now I know his name and face
and he knows my name and face.

545
00:38:40,527 --> 00:38:42,362
You see?
And I'm going to tell you something.

546
00:38:42,446 --> 00:38:44,156
That is how it should be.

547
00:38:49,286 --> 00:38:52,331
My son wanna open up
a snowball stand on the street.

548
00:38:52,414 --> 00:38:54,082
Do we need a permit for this?

549
00:38:56,668 --> 00:39:00,172
You ever seen a West Side
community meeting like this one?

550
00:39:00,255 --> 00:39:03,258
The folks downtown
tell me that stands aren't allowed

551
00:39:03,342 --> 00:39:05,344
in the city right-of-way at all.

552
00:39:05,427 --> 00:39:08,597
Now they do say it's possible
to have a snowball stand

553
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,349
behind the sidewalk.

554
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:19,107
Why are you really down here,
councilman?

555
00:39:19,942 --> 00:39:23,779
- I mean, this ain't even your district.
- I'm interested.

556
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:26,615
And I have the public safety subcommittee.

557
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,121
You see that building there?

558
00:39:34,790 --> 00:39:38,168
It was the old stryker building,
it was a funeral parlor.

559
00:39:38,460 --> 00:39:41,421
The last stop before the cemetery
for West Side white folk

560
00:39:41,505 --> 00:39:43,507
back when there were still some around.

561
00:39:43,590 --> 00:39:49,388
Right about the time that Jim crow
was breaking up back in the early '60s,

562
00:39:49,471 --> 00:39:52,224
somebody asked old man stryker,
they said, "stryker,

563
00:39:52,307 --> 00:39:57,020
"you gonna change your policy
and start burying black folk?"

564
00:39:57,104 --> 00:39:58,814
And stryker said,

565
00:39:58,981 --> 00:40:02,568
"yeah, on one condition.

566
00:40:02,651 --> 00:40:05,028
"That I can do them all at once."

567
00:40:08,073 --> 00:40:09,700
That's sick.

568
00:40:09,825 --> 00:40:14,079
But you know something?
I had a lot of respect for that man.

569
00:40:15,289 --> 00:40:16,999
'Cause, unlike most folks,

570
00:40:17,082 --> 00:40:19,543
I always knew where he stood.

571
00:40:19,835 --> 00:40:21,461
I'm doing my job.

572
00:40:27,801 --> 00:40:29,845
Look, I done showed you the good.

573
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:32,764
Come on, let me show you the ugly.

574
00:40:46,862 --> 00:40:48,322
Hey.

575
00:40:48,530 --> 00:40:51,450
- How come so quick?
- Stringer bell's given name.

576
00:40:51,700 --> 00:40:53,452
Russell.

577
00:40:53,535 --> 00:40:55,537
For now, Ahmed.

578
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:04,296
We're on the top of the mountain.

579
00:41:10,886 --> 00:41:14,264
Red tops over here.
Come get them, come get them.

580
00:41:26,568 --> 00:41:28,945
- This is it?
- One of three.

581
00:41:29,655 --> 00:41:31,990
How did you make this happen?

582
00:41:33,408 --> 00:41:35,410
I just did it.

583
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:40,832
I got tired of hearing folks
talk about what needed to be done

584
00:41:40,916 --> 00:41:43,960
or what they would do if it was up to them.

585
00:41:45,087 --> 00:41:48,840
So, this is about you making a Mark?

586
00:41:49,883 --> 00:41:53,470
No, I ain't analyzed it all that deep.

587
00:41:54,221 --> 00:41:56,890
I ain't claiming no
kind of victory, neither.

588
00:41:57,307 --> 00:42:00,602
I will say I'm glad I tried.

589
00:42:04,189 --> 00:42:08,568
Go on, councilman.
I'll wait for you down here.

590
00:42:09,986 --> 00:42:11,988
You're not coming?

591
00:42:13,365 --> 00:42:15,367
Now, what you gonna see ain't pretty.

592
00:42:15,450 --> 00:42:17,577
But it's safe.

593
00:42:18,995 --> 00:42:22,082
I think you need to take this journey
your own self.

594
00:42:22,541 --> 00:42:24,376
Yeah.

595
00:42:28,380 --> 00:42:31,508
Better deal on those yellow tops.
Yellow tops right here.

596
00:43:06,501 --> 00:43:10,338
- I ordered one for you.
- Thanks.

597
00:43:11,673 --> 00:43:13,967
- Surprised I called?
- A little.

598
00:43:14,968 --> 00:43:16,970
After the way we left it.

599
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:20,056
I'm a type a, Jimmy.

600
00:43:21,391 --> 00:43:23,393
People like me break things.

601
00:43:23,477 --> 00:43:27,147
When I slow down, or when I take
a minute to think about it, I...

602
00:43:29,524 --> 00:43:31,318
Is that your idea of an apology?

603
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:35,238
I didn't drive an hour up 95 to apologize.

604
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,242
I missed you.

605
00:43:43,997 --> 00:43:46,208
I missed you too, I guess.

606
00:43:46,291 --> 00:43:48,585
Seems a long way
to come just to tell me that,

607
00:43:48,668 --> 00:43:51,463
then turn around
and drive back down to DC.

608
00:43:51,546 --> 00:43:53,548
I'm not driving back tonight.

609
00:44:00,931 --> 00:44:03,350
So what's going on?
Are you working on a case?

610
00:44:03,433 --> 00:44:06,061
Mm-hm. It's a good one.

611
00:44:06,895 --> 00:44:10,023
How about you? Anything interesting?

612
00:44:10,106 --> 00:44:13,610
I did hear a crazy Baltimore story,

613
00:44:13,819 --> 00:44:16,822
you know,
through the rumor mill of Washington.

614
00:44:16,905 --> 00:44:19,074
- Really?
- Some...

615
00:44:19,866 --> 00:44:23,620
Renegade police commander
takes it on himself to...

616
00:44:23,829 --> 00:44:27,040
I don't know,
legalise drugs in the precinct?

617
00:44:27,123 --> 00:44:29,334
Mayor doesn't even know about it?

618
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:32,921
- Can you believe that?
- Crazy story.

619
00:44:33,004 --> 00:44:34,339
Someone...

620
00:44:35,507 --> 00:44:37,509
I think it's Colvin.

621
00:44:38,343 --> 00:44:40,345
You know him?

622
00:44:42,389 --> 00:44:44,391
No, I can't say that I do.

623
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:51,356
Still, I think it's funny that some
water-cooler talker down in DC

624
00:44:51,439 --> 00:44:53,567
knows any Baltimore cop's name.

625
00:44:56,945 --> 00:44:58,947
I was just wondering.

626
00:45:08,164 --> 00:45:09,916
Listen, I'm...

627
00:45:12,127 --> 00:45:14,546
- You're leaving?
- Yeah, I think so.

628
00:45:16,298 --> 00:45:18,133
Good night.

629
00:45:25,181 --> 00:45:27,475
Damn, man, I miss this crib already.

630
00:45:28,685 --> 00:45:32,689
Well, you spending a lot of time at the
other spot doing what you gotta do, huh?

631
00:45:32,772 --> 00:45:34,482
Yeah.

632
00:45:34,816 --> 00:45:37,736
Man, it's a shame we got to deal
with this marlo bullshit, man.

633
00:45:37,819 --> 00:45:42,198
- If I had taken care of that earlier, man...
- There's always gonna be a marlo, man.

634
00:45:42,407 --> 00:45:44,075
No marlo, no game.

635
00:45:45,577 --> 00:45:48,872
But you could've dealt with that shit
a little sooner, yeah,

636
00:45:48,955 --> 00:45:50,999
but don't let it lay on you like that.

637
00:45:51,458 --> 00:45:56,004
Tonight, I mean, I'm gonna kick back
and just enjoy this view.

638
00:45:57,339 --> 00:46:00,634
I mean, look at this shit.
Can you fucking believe this?

639
00:46:00,842 --> 00:46:04,930
I got a crib that's overlooking the harbor.
We used to run through this motherfucker,

640
00:46:05,013 --> 00:46:08,391
we had every security guard in there
following us.

641
00:46:08,475 --> 00:46:11,770
- As they should have.
- True, true.

642
00:46:11,853 --> 00:46:14,314
- And then there was that one time...
- Toy store?

643
00:46:14,397 --> 00:46:17,359
I told your ass
not to steal the badminton set.

644
00:46:17,442 --> 00:46:21,279
What you gonna do
with a fucking net and a racket

645
00:46:21,363 --> 00:46:23,406
and we ain't got no yard.

646
00:46:25,033 --> 00:46:28,578
You like, "yo, that white boy
ain't gonna chase after me."

647
00:46:28,662 --> 00:46:30,580
- He sure did, though.
- Then he's there.

648
00:46:30,664 --> 00:46:33,291
- I said, "what the fuck?"
- He was like Carl Lewis.

649
00:46:33,375 --> 00:46:35,085
Fists was balled up.

650
00:46:35,168 --> 00:46:37,504
Your ass was running too,
fast as you could.

651
00:46:37,587 --> 00:46:40,590
Punching yourself in the chest
looking all mad and shit. Argh!

652
00:46:40,674 --> 00:46:43,051
That shit was crazy, man.

653
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:46,429
Right here too, man, right there. Goddamn.

654
00:46:48,515 --> 00:46:51,017
Imagine, if! Had the money that I have now,

655
00:46:51,101 --> 00:46:54,187
I could have bought
half this waterfront property.

656
00:46:54,270 --> 00:46:56,106
God damn it.

657
00:46:57,399 --> 00:46:59,567
Forget about that for a while, man.

658
00:47:00,944 --> 00:47:02,946
You know, just dream with me.

659
00:47:06,074 --> 00:47:08,243
We ain't gotta dream no more, man.

660
00:47:10,954 --> 00:47:12,872
We got real shit,

661
00:47:12,956 --> 00:47:15,500
real estate, that we can touch.

662
00:47:23,133 --> 00:47:25,343
I can't get too fucked up tonight, man.

663
00:47:25,427 --> 00:47:28,013
I got some shit
I gotta do on the site tomorrow.

664
00:47:28,096 --> 00:47:33,018
Plus, the fucking polack
we got working for us, man,

665
00:47:33,101 --> 00:47:35,186
I gotta pull his coat.

666
00:47:35,270 --> 00:47:37,772
If he had anything to do
with that Clay Davis bullshit,

667
00:47:37,856 --> 00:47:40,567
I'm gonna have to cut his money,
little faggot.

668
00:47:41,568 --> 00:47:43,445
What time y'all meeting?

669
00:47:49,409 --> 00:47:53,830
What time? 12, I think. Why?

670
00:47:53,913 --> 00:47:56,249
You need me to do something for you?

671
00:47:57,709 --> 00:48:00,670
No, I'm just seeing
where you going to be at.

672
00:48:02,255 --> 00:48:04,424
You need to relax more, man.

673
00:48:07,177 --> 00:48:10,472
Well, when the time is right, I will.

674
00:48:12,474 --> 00:48:15,143
You know,
I don't take my work too seriously.

675
00:48:16,895 --> 00:48:18,521
That's right.

676
00:48:21,149 --> 00:48:22,817
It's just business.

677
00:48:32,494 --> 00:48:34,829
Us, motherfucker.

678
00:48:38,166 --> 00:48:39,834
Us, man.

679
00:49:19,374 --> 00:49:22,127
Get him, Andre, go get him.

680
00:49:22,210 --> 00:49:25,130
Come on, spider, you gotta swing on him.

681
00:49:27,215 --> 00:49:29,008
Easy, easy, easy.

682
00:49:29,551 --> 00:49:32,345
- All right?
- I'm good, I'm good.

683
00:49:32,887 --> 00:49:34,727
- Ditty, you up.
- Why didn't you hit him back?

684
00:49:34,764 --> 00:49:36,558
You, Justin.

685
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:40,103
Come on, boy, I'm calling your name.

686
00:49:44,065 --> 00:49:47,026
Listen up.
We gonna have three two-minute rounds.

687
00:49:47,110 --> 00:49:49,904
Watch the low blows. Touch gloves.

688
00:49:54,200 --> 00:49:55,493
And...

689
00:49:56,411 --> 00:49:58,329
Let's go, Justin.

690
00:49:58,413 --> 00:50:00,957
Justin, come on.

691
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:02,667
That's good, that's good.

692
00:50:02,876 --> 00:50:04,878
Straight shot, come on.

693
00:50:04,961 --> 00:50:06,838
Keep your hands up, Justin.

694
00:50:06,921 --> 00:50:09,507
- Come on, man. Come on.
- You gotta block that.

695
00:50:09,591 --> 00:50:14,345
He leading left and punching right, Justin.
Move towards his weak side.

696
00:50:14,429 --> 00:50:17,015
- He only come up to your waist.
- Man, bell.

697
00:50:19,017 --> 00:50:21,394
- That was a quick two minutes.
- Yeah, I know.

698
00:50:21,477 --> 00:50:24,147
Get you some water, boy, and spit it out.

699
00:50:27,108 --> 00:50:29,235
- You all right?
- Dizzy.

700
00:50:29,319 --> 00:50:32,447
That's why the hell
I keep telling you you got to breathe, boy.

701
00:50:32,530 --> 00:50:34,324
So, what? You had enough?

702
00:50:34,407 --> 00:50:37,410
- No, I'm good.
- All right, all right.

703
00:50:39,120 --> 00:50:41,289
- Let's go, Justin.
- Let's go, Justin!

704
00:50:44,959 --> 00:50:47,462
Jab, Justin. Gotta jab.

705
00:50:52,300 --> 00:50:54,302
Hm.

706
00:51:01,935 --> 00:51:04,187
Hey, we're up. Here it is.

707
00:51:04,437 --> 00:51:06,231
- It's me, man.
- You heard from the fat man?

708
00:51:06,314 --> 00:51:08,066
- Yeah.
- We low, right?

709
00:51:08,149 --> 00:51:11,069
- One Mark shy of the Mark.
- Yeah, it's light.

710
00:51:11,152 --> 00:51:14,530
- Cherry say it's light.
- Tell the man I'm doing what needs doing.

711
00:51:14,614 --> 00:51:18,034
All right, I'll tell him.
Oh, and that other thing?

712
00:51:18,117 --> 00:51:20,328
- What?
- Them two hitters you asked after.

713
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:22,997
- They good with it.
- Not on the phone.

714
00:51:25,625 --> 00:51:28,962
- That's it.
- We got it!

715
00:51:35,468 --> 00:51:37,470
Good work.

716
00:51:40,348 --> 00:51:42,517
I guess this is pertinent.

717
00:52:11,587 --> 00:52:15,800
Ain't no need to go back out.
You ain't got to prove nothing.

718
00:52:15,883 --> 00:52:20,305
Shoot, my momma hit me harder than that.
I still got a chance, he getting tired.

719
00:52:20,388 --> 00:52:22,056
Drink and spit.

720
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:27,478
- Ready.
- You more than ready, boy.

721
00:52:27,687 --> 00:52:30,189
You game, rooster.

722
00:52:30,273 --> 00:52:32,692
Let's go, Justin!

723
00:52:47,457 --> 00:52:51,919
- Is there an alley entrance?
- Boarded up on both sides.

724
00:52:52,003 --> 00:52:55,173
So we gonna have to go through the front.

725
00:52:55,256 --> 00:52:57,508
That's a change for you, isn't it?

726
00:52:59,052 --> 00:53:02,555
You just be ready, bow tie.
You know what I'm talking about?

727
00:53:11,105 --> 00:53:12,732
Breathe, boy. Breathe.

728
00:53:19,947 --> 00:53:21,449
Touch gloves.

729
00:53:27,288 --> 00:53:29,874
- How'd I do?
- You still got plenty to learn.

730
00:53:29,957 --> 00:53:33,294
But on the heart side? You did good.

731
00:53:38,257 --> 00:53:40,968
Go on home, soldier. You done for the day.

732
00:53:48,226 --> 00:53:49,811
I can see it all clearly now.

733
00:53:49,894 --> 00:53:52,855
Between you and them subcontractors
and that motherfucking politician,

734
00:53:52,939 --> 00:53:54,232
y'all had me in a spin, right?

735
00:53:54,315 --> 00:53:56,901
- Mr. Bell, I don't know...
- Little man!

736
00:53:56,984 --> 00:54:00,655
We gonna get all this shit sorted out.
And if the shit don't come up right,

737
00:54:00,822 --> 00:54:03,199
one way or another
you gonna pay for this shit.

738
00:54:03,282 --> 00:54:06,869
I understand you're angry
but we've made progress in here.

739
00:54:06,953 --> 00:54:09,914
I don't know what passed
between you and senator Davis,

740
00:54:09,997 --> 00:54:12,333
but if you're unhappy
with Clayton's performance...

741
00:54:14,502 --> 00:54:17,004
- Shit.
- Oh, god.

742
00:54:17,964 --> 00:54:19,424
Oh, god, no.

743
00:54:25,638 --> 00:54:28,057
God, no.

744
00:55:00,381 --> 00:55:02,383
I ain't strapped.

745
00:55:06,637 --> 00:55:10,099
Look, man, I ain't involved.

746
00:55:10,892 --> 00:55:13,895
I ain't involved
in that gangster bullshit no more.

747
00:55:21,152 --> 00:55:24,489
What y'all niggers want, man?
Huh? Money?

748
00:55:29,118 --> 00:55:31,078
Is that it?

749
00:55:32,038 --> 00:55:35,666
'Cause if it is, man,
I can be a better friend to y'all alive.

750
00:55:38,044 --> 00:55:40,213
You still don't get it, do you?

751
00:55:41,923 --> 00:55:43,966
This ain't about your money, bro.

752
00:55:44,926 --> 00:55:47,178
Your boy gave you up.

753
00:55:48,471 --> 00:55:52,433
That's right. And we ain't
had to torture his ass, neither.

754
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:10,868
It seem like...

755
00:56:11,619 --> 00:56:14,247
I can't say nothing to change y'all minds.

756
00:56:27,093 --> 00:56:29,011
Well, get on with it, mother...

